<!DOCTYPE html>
<html xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal">
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <title>CommitteeSpot - The simplest way for teams to review job applicants, nominations, proposals, etc. online</title>

    <meta name="description" content="CommitteeSpot helps teams make decisions by facilitating 
                                      selection processes online. Whether you're hiring employees,
                                      reviewing award nominations, or selecting a prize race horse,
                                      CommitteeSpot can help.">

    <link rel="shortcut icon" href="/static/images/favicon.png" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/static/bootstrap/css/bootstrap.css" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/static/css/cs.css" />

    <script type="text/javascript" src="https://www.google.com/jsapi?key=ABQIAAAAYSkItflLWuecB8KaSnAoYBR9oVpe_xR_xcjrBDusQLi3eQlQ5RQJKyrcXPg_qXpQTcL7nfrqU3PhaA"></script>
    <script type="text/javascript">
        google.load("jquery", "1.7.1");
        google.load("jqueryui", "1.8.16");
    </script>  
    <script type="text/javascript" src="/static/bootstrap/js/bootstrap.js"></script>
</head>
<body tal:define="user request.user">

<div id="header_homepage" class="container">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="span12">
            <div id="menu">
                <a tal:condition="user" 
                   tal:attributes="href route_url('project:list', request)">my projects</a>
                <a tal:attributes="href route_url('project:add',request)">new project</a>
                <a tal:condition="user" 
                   tal:attributes="href route_url('user:profile', request, user_id=user.id)">my profile</a>
                <a tal:condition="not user or user.is_temporary()" 
                   tal:attributes="href route_url('auth:login', request)">sign in</a>
                <a tal:condition="user and not user.is_temporary()" 
                   tal:attributes="href route_url('auth:logout', request)">sign out</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div id="mast">
    <div class="container">
        <img src="/static/images/mast_logo.png" alt="CommitteeSpot" height="105" width="460" >
        <h2>The simple way for your team to review anything online.</h2>
        <a href="${route_url('project:add', request)}" class="btn btn-huge btn-primary">
            Get Started Now!
            <div class="tiny">one project free, no signup to start</div>
        </a>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="container page">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="span8">

            <h2>Make decisions, not busy work</h2>

            <img src="/static/images/diagram_small.png" width="232" height="127" alt="Process Diagram"
                 class="home-image-right" >

            <div class="padding" style="margin-right: 240px;">

                <p>
                    You want to hire someone or select a proposal, not spend time routing 
                    records to your team, sending reminders, and correlating feedback.
                </p>
        
                <p>
                    CommitteeSpot elimnates the busy work of team based decisions! No more
                    mess of email, surveys, and intranets.
                </p>

            </div>

            <h2>Review anything</h2>

            <img src="/static/images/types.png" width="232" height="127" alt="Types of review processes"
                 class="home-image-left" >

            <div class="padding" style="margin-left: 240px;">
                <p>
                    Whether your team is hiring a contractor or choosing a venue for
                    an awards banquet CommitteeSpot can help.
                </p>

                <p>
                    Committee Spot is populated with templates for commonly reviewed documents or
                    you can create your own.
                </p>

                <p>
                    If you need feedback from your team to review anything
                    <a href="${route_url('project:add',request)}">try it out.</a>
                </p>

            </div>

            <h2>Simple pricing plans</h2>

            <div class="padding" style="padding: 20px 50px;">
                <table class="table" id="pricing">
                <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Tiny</th>
                    <th>Small</th>
                    <th>Medium</th>
                </tr>
                </thead>

                <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td>1 <small>administrator</small></td>
                    <td>1 <small>administrator</small></td>
                    <td>5 <small>administrators</small></td>
                </tr>

                <tr>
                    <td>5 <small>team members</small></td>
                    <td>20 <small>team members</small></td>
                    <td>50 <small>team members</small></td>
                </tr>

                <tr>
                    <td>1 <small>project at a time</small></td>
                    <td>5 <small>projects at a time</small></td>
                    <td>20 <small>projects at a time</small></td>
                </tr>

                <tr>
                    <td>n/a</td>
                    <td colspan="2"> 
                        Collect applications and nominations online<br >
                        Collect public/anonymous feedback<br >
                        Custom logos and branding
                    </td>
                </tr>

                <tr>
                    <td><a href="#" class="btn btn-success" style="width: 90%;"><strong>FREE!</strong> <small>get started now</small></a></td>
                    <td><a class="btn disabled" style="width: 90%">Coming Soon! <small>per month</small></a></td>
                    <td><a class="btn disabled" style="width: 90%">Coming Soon! <small>per month</small></a></td>
                </tr>
                </tbody>
                </table>

            </div>

        </div> <!-- end span7 -->

        <div class="span4">

            <h2>5 simple steps</h2>

            <div class="padding" id="simple-steps">
            
                <h3 id="icon-items">Add items</h3>

                <p>
                    Create employment applications, project ideas, proposals, bids 
                    or anything you need a team to review. Each item can range from a single file
                    to a complex data record. You decide what information your team
                    needs to see.
                </p>

                <h3 id="icon-feedback">Create a feedback form</h3>

                <p>
                    Setup questions for your team to answer about each item. "Should we 
                    consider this candidate?", "Pursue this project?", "Rank this proposal". 
                    Again, you control the feedback.
                </p>

                <h3 id="icon-team">Add your team</h3>

                <p>
                    Enter an e-mail address for each team member. A secure account
                    is generated for each member of your team.
                </p>

                <h3 id="icon-team">Distribute</h3>

                <p>
                    Once everything is ready to go distribute items to your
                    team with a single click. Notification and reminder e-mails 
                    with review instructions are automatically sent to the team.
                </p>

                <h3 id="icon-decide" >Get results, make decisions</h3>

                <p>
                    Easily view the feedback from your team online or export it to 
                    Microsoft Excel for powerful analysis.
                </p>

            </div>
        </div> <!-- end span5 -->
    </div>
</div>

<div class="container" id="box-row">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="span4">
            <div class="page">
                <h2>Service and support</h2>
                <div class="padding">
                    <p>
                        We want you to love CommitteeSpot.
                        If you ever need help, have a complaint,
                        or an idea for a new feature we want to know
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        <a href="mailto:team@committeespot.com">Send us e-mail</a>
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="span4">
            <div class="page">
                <h2>Free to use</h2>
                <div class="padding">
                    <p>
                        You get one free project, no credit card required. You don't need
                        an account to get started.
                    </p>

                    <a href="${route_url('project:add',request)}">Create your project</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="span4">
            <div class="page">
                <h2>Watch the demo</h2>
                <div class="padding">
                    <p>Video</p>

                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="container">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="span12">
            <div id="footer">
                <a href="${route_url('terms', request)}">terms</a> |
                <a href="${route_url('privacy', request)}">privacy</a> |
                <a href="mailto:team@committeespot.com">contact us</a> | 
                <span>copyright &copy; 2012 committeespot llc</span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<script type="text/javascript">

  var _gaq = _gaq || [];
  _gaq.push(['_setAccount', 'UA-29691323-1']);
  _gaq.push(['_setDomainName', 'committeespot.com']);
  _gaq.push(['_trackPageview']);

  (function() {
    var ga = document.createElement('script'); ga.type = 'text/javascript'; ga.async = true;
    ga.src = ('https:' == document.location.protocol ? 'https://ssl' : 'http://www') + '.google-analytics.com/ga.js';
    var s = document.getElementsByTagName('script')[0]; s.parentNode.insertBefore(ga, s);
  })();

</script>

</body>
</html>

